The following code creates two sensors to measure battery input/outpt kWh. The goal is to get the following sensors: 
- 1. total amount of battery input kWh
- 2. total amount of battery output kWh



Based on that you can create dialy utility meter. 

I know this solution is not perfect, because if the state switches from "idle" to "charging"/"discharging" and the "battery_energy_level" sensor changes as well at the same time, I think total amount is not counted.
I think the state has to be "charging"/"discharging" before the value of battery_energy_level changes. But at least it's 95% problem solved. 
<code>
- trigger:
    - platform: state
      entity_id: sensor.pv_anlage_battery_energy_level
  sensor:
    - name: "Battery charge delta"
      unique_id: battery_charge_delta
      unit_of_measurement: "kWh"
      device_class: energy
      state_class: total
      state: >
          {% set new = trigger.to_state.state | float(0) %}
          {% set old = trigger.from_state.state | float(0) %}
          {% set diff = new - old %}
          {% set last = states('sensor.battery_charge_delta') | float(0) %}
          {% if states('sensor.qcells_battery_charging_state') == 'charging' and diff > 0 %}
            {{ (last + diff) | round(3) }}
          {% else %}
            {{ last | round(3) }}
          {% endif %}

    - name: "Battery discharge delta"
      unique_id: battery_discharge_delta
      unit_of_measurement: "kWh"
      device_class: energy
      state_class: total
      state: >
          {% set new = trigger.to_state.state | float(0) %}
          {% set old = trigger.from_state.state | float(0) %}
          {% set diff = new - old %}
          {% set last = states('sensor.battery_discharge_delta') | float(0) %}
          {% if states('sensor.qcells_battery_charging_state') == 'discharging' and diff < 0 %}
            {{ (last + (diff * -1)) | round(3) }}
          {% else %}
            {{ last | round(3) }}
          {% endif %}
